ai_spell_check_issues.description: While 'Обриши' can mean 'delete' in some contexts (primarily when referring to erasing something), it's more commonly used for 'wipe' or 'erase'. 'Delete' implies a more permanent removal, which 'Обриши' doesn't always convey. A more precise translation depending on the context would be 'Избриши' (Izbriši).

The Serbian translation 'Obriši' is the imperative form (you delete) and might not be appropriate depending on the context. 'Delete' can also refer to the action of deleting, not a command to delete. A more neutral translation might be 'Brisanje'.
